{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":522595,"duration_api_ms":602594,"num_turns":58,"result":"All changes implemented and validated. Here's the JSON response:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"change_summary\": \"Fixed 3 milestone lineage issues: (1) Added round-trip tests in fs.rs that assert StartJournalDetails and CompletionJournalDetails stay in sync with their model.rs render counterparts — any field drift will cause test failure. (2) Changed update_task_run in fs.rs to accept a single open runless entry when a run_id is supplied, enabling backfill instead of rejecting with a CorruptRecord error; conflicting plan_hash values still block finalization. (3) Added plan_hash auto-population from the milestone snapshot in service.rs record_bead_start and update_task_run — when callers omit plan_hash, the snapshot's stored value (set by persist_plan) is forwarded to the lineage layer. Updated 1 existing test whose assertion changed from rejection to plan_hash conflict detection.\",\n  \"steps\": [\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Issue 1: Added round-trip sync tests (start_journal_details_round_trips_with_model_render and completion_journal_details_round_trips_with_model_render) in src/adapters/fs.rs test module that render via model.rs, parse via fs.rs structs, and assert field-level equality plus render stability\",\n      \"order\": 1,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Issue 2: Changed the [index] if entries[*index].run_id.is_none() arm at fs.rs:3018 from returning CorruptRecord error to accepting the runless match, allowing run_id backfill during finalization. Existing plan_hash conflict and option_conflicts checks still guard against invalid transitions\",\n      \"order\": 2,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Issue 3: Added effective_plan_hash resolution in service.rs record_bead_start (line 428) and update_task_run (line 561) that reads snapshot.plan_hash as fallback when caller supplies None. Explicit caller-provided plan_hash takes precedence via map().or_else() chain\",\n      \"order\": 3,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Updated existing test completion_with_named_run_id_requires_exact_attempt_match → renamed to completion_with_conflicting_plan_hash_rejects_runless_match, asserting plan_hash conflict error instead of legacy runless rejection\",\n      \"order\": 4,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Added 3 new service-level tests: runless_start_completed_with_named_run_id (Issue 2 happy path), plan_hash_auto_populated_from_snapshot (Issue 3 with persist_plan → omitted plan_hash), explicit_plan_hash_takes_precedence_over_snapshot (Issue 3 precedence)\",\n      \"order\": 5,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Ran cargo test (683 passed, 0 failed), cargo clippy -- -D warnings (clean), cargo fmt --check (modified files clean, pre-existing agent_execution_test.rs formatting unrelated)\",\n      \"order\": 6,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"validation_evidence\": [\n    \"cargo test: 683 passed, 0 failed, 0 ignored\",\n    \"cargo clippy -- -D warnings: no warnings or errors on modified crate\",\n    \"cargo fmt --check: service.rs and fs.rs pass; only pre-existing formatting diffs in unrelated tests/unit/agent_execution_test.rs\",\n    \"start_journal_details_round_trips_with_model_render: verifies all 3 fields (project_id, run_id, plan_hash) survive render→parse→render cycle\",\n    \"completion_journal_details_round_trips_with_model_render: verifies all 6 fields survive render→parse→render cycle\",\n    \"runless_start_completed_with_named_run_id: starts with run_id=None, completes with run_id=Some('run-late'), verifies backfill and outcome\",\n    \"plan_hash_auto_populated_from_snapshot: persists plan, starts bead with plan_hash=None, verifies snapshot plan_hash appears in lineage entry\",\n    \"explicit_plan_hash_takes_precedence_over_snapshot: persists plan, starts bead with explicit hash, verifies caller value wins over snapshot\",\n    \"completion_with_conflicting_plan_hash_rejects_runless_match: verifies plan_hash conflict still prevents invalid finalization after runless acceptance\"\n  ],\n  \"outstanding_risks\": [\n    \"The round-trip tests detect field-level drift at test time, not compile time. A field addition that is only used in a code path not covered by tests could still silently drift until the round-trip test catches the serialization mismatch. A derive-macro or build-script approach would catch it at compile time but is heavier-weight.\",\n    \"Pre-existing formatting drift in tests/unit/agent_execution_test.rs is unrelated to these changes but will appear in cargo fmt --check across the full workspace.\"\n  ]\n}\n```","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"dc6aa508-19dd-4e12-bdf9-726d7fd9c018","total_cost_usd":2.7801459499999996,"usage":{"input_tokens":46,"cache_creation_input_tokens":74092,"cache_read_input_tokens":2705769,"output_tokens":17931,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":74092,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":288,"outputTokens":15493,"cacheReadInputTokens":2479797,"cacheCreationInputTokens":151959,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.5156814500000001,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000},"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":46,"outputTokens":17931,"cacheReadInputTokens":2705769,"cacheCreationInputTokens":74092,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":2.2644644999999994,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"951245c2-8db1-4f12-bbed-810a9ef928c9"}
